               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. WRIGHT</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18670819-name-600" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18670819-name-600" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18670819-name-600" type="surname" value="PEARCE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18670819-name-600" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN PEARCE.</persName>
                  </hi> I am assistant to Mr. John Stone, of 75, Plumstead Road—on Saturday, 3rd August, I put a piece of holland in the shop door—it was about forty yards and was worth 20<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—I missed it on Monday morning—I saw it about twelve o'clock an Saturday—this ticket (<hi rend="italic">prod<lb></lb>uced</hi>. was on the holland—I pinned it on—it is the property of Mr. Stone—the prisoner had no authority to remove it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18670819-name-601" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18670819-name-601" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18670819-name-601" type="surname" value="CROUGH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18670819-name-601" type="given" value="JAMES WILLIAM"></interp>JAMES WILLIAM CROUGH</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">Detective Officer</hi>. On Saturday, the 3rd August, I saw the prisoner about 150 yards from the railway station at Plumstead; that is eight miles from Mr. Stone's shop—he was carrying a black bag—I ran across the road and laid hold of him, and asked what he had there—he made no reply—I opened the bag and found this holland (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>.—he said some man had given it to him—when I caught him he put his hand in his pocket—I opened his hand and found the ticket produced.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi>. met a man who asked me to carry this, and gave me the holland. When I was stopped this man was behind me.</p>
